---
layout: post
title: UniFi UAP/LongRange/Pro Setup
description: Documentation for Cucumber Tony's Cloud Wi-Fi Platform
---

<p>Here's what you'll receive:</p>

<ul>
<li>Instruction Card
<li>UniFi AP
<li>PoE injector and power cable
<li>Wall mounting accessories, including screws
</ul>

<p>What you'll need:</p>

<ul>
<li>Power socket
<li>A working broadband connection
<li>Your modem
<li>Cucumber Tony account
<li>2 X Ethernet Cables
<li>Switch (optional, if you need additional ports - please note that the UniFi access point only has one port)
</ul>

<div class="text-center">
<img src="/images/setup/unifi-ap/unifi-content.jpg">
</div>

<h3>Plugging it all in</h3>
<hr>

<p>Plug the power cable into the PoE injector, and then connect it to a power socket.</p>

<p>Then, connect an Ethernet Cable between your PoE injectorâ€™s LAN port, and a LAN port on your modem.</p>

<div class="text-center">
<img src="/images/setup/unifi-ap/lan-connect.jpg">
</div>

<p>Next, connect your second Ethernet Cable between the PoE port on the PoE injector and the port on your UniFi AP. You can find this at the back of your UniFi access point.</p>

<p>When it's all plugged in, it should look similar to the image below. Your UniFi AP will light up when you've turned on the power supply. Just follow the adding a box guide to add your box into Cucumber Tony.</p>

<div class="text-center">
<img src="/images/setup/unifi-ap/unifi-powered.jpg">
</div>

<h2>Congrats! Now you just need to head into your Cucumber Tony dashboard and add in your lovely new box, <a href="https://my.ctapp.io/?data-elevio-article=7107#/">click here to get started!</a></h2>

<hr>

<p>If you only have one spare port at the back of your modem and need extra ports for other devices, it is advised to buy a switch.</p>

<h3><b>WARNING</b></h3>
<p><b>Please use the power supply provided to you. An incorrect power supply may cause the fuse in the box to blow, breaking your box and warranty.</b></p>
